column3: ACDC Express is South Africa’s largest independent wholesale supplier of electronic goods and South Africa’s largest electrical retail franchise.
Based in Chicago, Illinois, the Adler Planetarium hosts more than half a million visitors each year and reaches millions more through youth STEM programs and other outreach projects.

Since 1970, Aerotech has designed and manufactured the highest performance motion control, positioning tables/stages, and positioning systems for our customers in industry, government, science, and research institutions around the world.
Japan's All Nippon Airways is now en route to the digital cloud.
Amstelring delivers care services for the elderly and disabled throughout the greater Amsterdam region with 4,000 full- and part-time employees.

Andela is solving the technical talent shortage by building distributed engineering teams with Africa's top software developers. In four years, Andela has hired 1,000 developers and become known as the "Best Place to Work in Africa," with tech campuses in Lagos, Nairobi, Kampala, and Kigali. Andela developers work as full-time engineers with companies ranging from the Fortune 500 to high-growth startups like Gusto and Cloudflare. Backed by Chan Zuckerberg Initiative, GV, and Spark Capital, Andela is powering global engineering teams while catalyzing the growth of tech ecosystems across Africa.

Founded as AdAsia Holdings in April 2016, the organization became AnyMind Group in January 2018 and is now the parent company of AdAsia Holdings, TalentMind, and CastingAsia. AnyMind Group aims to provide industries, businesses, and professionals with a suite of AI-based solutions to enable growth. Headquartered in Singapore, AnyMind Group has over 330 staff across 13 offices in 11 markets in Asia.

Ascend Money is one of South East Asia's largest fintech businesses and uses digital technologies to provide financial services to people in the region – particularly those who lack access to banking. Its offerings include the TrueMoney regional payment platform for underserved and digital consumers. The TrueMoney platform supports more than 40 million consumers across six countries: Cambodia, Indonesia, Myanmar, the Philippines, Thailand, and Vietnam. TrueMoney also provides an e-wallet app that provides easy ways of topping up mobile phones, shopping online and paying for products and services; a network of 65,000 branded shops; and international remittances, initially between Thailand and Myanmar. In addition, Ascend Money offers financial products to small to medium businesses.

As part of its customer-centric attitude and mandate to transform banking, ATB launched a bold transformation initiative powered by G Suite. This has resulted in ATB driving innovation, optimizing workflows and business processes, and enabling more positive customer interactions.

Founded 16 years ago, Atlassian is a globally distributed maker of software that helps teams collaborate more effectively. The business has about 3,200 full-time employees plus about 800 contractors and contingent workers.
AVEVE Group is a Belgian full-service supplier to farmers. As a market leader, the company is able to offer top expertise and the widest possible portfolio of products and services to its clients.
BBVA banks on G Suite to transform its business.
Banco de Crédito e Inversiones (Bci) is one of Chile’s largest banks, with more than 10,000 employees and branches in Latin America and the United States.
Gruppo BPER is Italy’s sixth largest Group, providing services to 2.3 million customers through a network of more than 1,170 branches nationwide.

Britam is a leading insurance provider in Kenya, offering insurance, investment, and real estate solutions to support clients at every stage of their lives. Since 2010, Britam has operated in seven countries in East and Central Africa.
Broadcom Inc. (NASDAQ: AVGO) is a leading designer, developer, and global supplier of a broad range of digital and analog semiconductor connectivity solutions.
Buffalo Tours stays on top of customers’ queries with Gmail. With G Suite, they achieved a 10% - 15% increase in efficiency and productivity gains and 17% year-on-year in cost savings as a business.
Established in 2006, Buurtzorg is a pioneering healthcare organization with a nurse-led model of holistic care that revolutionized community care in the Netherlands.

In 1991, the Canada Games Council was incorporated as a private, non-profit governing body responsible for the ongoing development of the Canada Games. As the Games move from one host community to the next, the Council supports host societies in key areas such as technical, planning, ceremonies and protocol, marketing, and sponsorship for sports.

Canam Group specializes in designing integrated solutions and fabricating customized products for the North American construction industry. Each year, Canam Group takes part in an average of 10,000 building, structural steel, and bridge projects, which can also include the supply of preconstruction, project management, and erection services. The company operates 25 plants across North America and employs more than 4,700 people in Canada, the United States, Romania, and India.

Founded in 2014, Cargills Bank provides a range of personal and business banking services to residents of Sri Lanka through 20 branches, the internet, and mobile banking. In addition, through agency banking at Cargills Food City Supermarkets, customers have access to over 370 service points.
Celestica is a multinational electronics manufacturing and supply chain services company.
Cello Zorg provides support in the Netherlands for people with intellectual disabilities, offering services from daycare to residencies to more than 1,600 clients.
Centro Medico Santagostino connects Italian private healthcare providers with over 240,000 patients, using cutting-edge communications to make services affordable.
CENTURY 21 is one of the largest, most recognizable residential real estate brands in the world with 9,400 offices across 80 countries.
Chas Everitt International Property Group is one of South Africa’s leading franchised real estate networks, with over 120 agencies.
As the fourth largest city in Tennessee, the City of Chattanooga provides local services to nearly 180,000 residents daily.

The City of Los Angeles Information Technology Agency (ITA) develops the IT infrastructure and applications that serve and inform the 4 million residents of Los Angeles. ITA has been instrumental in earning Los Angeles honors as the top digital city of 2017 and 2016 from The Center for Digital Government, and recognition for its data-driven city initiative in February 2018 from The Bloomberg Foundation.
Founded in 1876, Paris-based Chantelle Lingerie designs, produces, and sells women’s lingerie through a global portfolio of premium lingerie brands.

Clarkstown Police Department serves the 85,000 citizens of Clarkstown, in Rockland County, New York. It has 156 sworn police officers and 70 civilians and crossing guards, working together to keep the community safe.

Colgate-Palmolive products are trusted by millions worldwide to care for their families and homes. Headquartered in New York City, the company focuses on manufacturing and distributing oral care, personal care, home care, and pet nutrition products.
Comanche County Memorial Hospital is the largest county community hospital in Oklahoma. It employs nearly 2,000 people, has 250 providers, and enjoys the benefit of approximately 100 volunteers.

Comune di Bologna is the local government of Bologna, the capital of Italy’s Emilia-Romagna region. As an important agricultural, industrial, financial, and transport hub, Bologna is home to the headquarters of many large companies.

Conrad Electronic is a German online retailer of electronic products based in Hirschau, Bavaria, with approximately 4,000 employees in the Conrad group. It offers more than 1 million products for B2B customers and 750,000 products for B2C customers, including computing equipment, multimedia, modeling, home automation, tools, electronic components, batteries, and power and motoring products.
G Suite enables Curves Taiwan to continue its rapid expansion.

Custom Ink is the leader in custom apparel and accessories for groups, events, and special occasions. It helps group organizers bring their families, friends, teammates, and colleagues together with inspired designs they are proud to wear. The company was founded in 2000.
Banco Davivienda is Colombia’s third largest bank, with more than 10 million customers. Established over 40 years ago, it has operations in 6 countries including the United States.
DB Corp is India’s largest newspaper publisher delivering 62 editions in four languages and selling about 6 million copies per day. The business also has an extensive online and mobile presence.

column3: Food-delivery service Deliveroo provides an app that connects restaurants, couriers, and hungry people in over 200 cities worldwide. Founded in 2013, Deliveroo is active in 14 countries.
G Suite is the perfect fit for modern furniture and design store, Design Within Reach.

Present in 18 countries across the world and drawing on more than 20 years of experience, Devoteam’s mission is to shape technology for the good of people. With more than 7,000 IT professionals, Devoteam provides the experience and expertise to ensure successful execution of its programs and make digital transformation a reality for companies big and small.
DFS is a UK-based retailer specializing in made-to-order furniture. DFS celebrated its 50th anniversary in 2019 with double-digit growth in online sales.

Dr. Agarwal’s Eye Hospital specializes in treating eye conditions such as cataracts; glaucoma; corneal problems such as ulcers, inflammation, and thinning; and retinal issues such as degeneration and detachment. The business operates 62 hospitals in cities across India and 14 hospitals in 8 countries in Africa, including Zambia, Nigeria, and Ghana.

DTDC Express is one of India’s leading express parcel service providers and operates one of the largest parcel delivery networks in India. Established in 1990 and headquartered at Bengaluru, DTDC operates seven zonal offices, 20 regional offices, and more than 522 facilities across India. Through its own operations, joint ventures, and business associations, DTDC’s footprint extends across Australia, Canada, China, Singapore and major Asian countries, the United Arab Emirates, the United Kingdom, and the United States.
Eaux de Vienne is a public sector partnership that manages water production, supply, and clean up in La Vienne, an administrative region between Bordeaux and Paris.

eir is Ireland’s principal provider of fixed line telecommunications services with a full range of voice, data, broadband, and TV services connecting more than 2 million customers whether they live in big cities or small villages.

Electronica Finance Limited (EFL) is a nonbank financial company (NBFC) that offers machine loans to help micro, small, and medium-sized businesses (MSMEs) purchase machinery and industrial property, gain access to working capital, or expand their business. With almost three decades of financial advisory and loan planning under its belt, the company today serves 7,500 customers across India, helping to create more success stories for businesses every day.

Entelgy, The BusinessTech Consultancy, is a transformation accelerator for companies looking to remain competitive in a constantly changing world. Inspiring and giving new solutions to the teams with which it co-creates and works, Entelgy helps with the adoption of new technologies to effect change while cyber-protecting assets.
Founded in 1962, EULEN is a global group present in 14 countries providing healthcare and social services to the private and public sector.
Founded in 1982, French company Euroclean offers its clients a broad range of cleaning services from general office cleaning to the most technical industrial cleaning.
With 100 years of service to homebuyers and companies, The F.C. Tucker Company is the most prolific independent real estate firm in the state of Indiana.
Founded in 1969, Italy’s Feralpi Group is one of the main steel producers in Europe, specializing in steel for the construction industry.
Fleetsmith provides a highly secure, cloud-based solution for managing a company’s macOS computers which fully integrates with G Suite.
Operating in 14 countries, FM Logistic provides supply chain solutions including manufacturing, warehousing, distribution, and optimization.
Based in Sweden, Footway is an online shoe retail platform connecting footwear manufacturers with customers in 11 European countries.
GANT is an international lifestyle brand founded in 1949 and headquartered in Stockholm.

General Mobile is a smartphone brand founded in 2005. Today, it is Turkey's largest Android manufacturer, cooperating with some of the world's major brands, such as Google, Foxconn, Qualcomm, Corning, Sony, Panasonic, Sharp, and Wacom.
Generali Hungary is one of the leading insurance companies in Hungary, providing both life, health, motor, homeower, and other insurance to its 876,000 customers.

Founded in 1995, Geneva Business School (GBS) has developed into a leader in Swiss quality education with a purpose to educate future business leaders. With an international approach and passion for excellence, GBS helps students reach their full potential and build real business connections.

Part of the $400 million Kallash Group, Genus Power Infrastructures has two business divisions offering solutions to the power sector. The Metering Solution Division provides a wide range of electricity meters, while the Engineering Construction and Contracts Division undertakes turnkey power projects such as installing substations, laying of transmission and distribution lines, rural electrification, and switchyard and network refurbishments.
GF Hoteles manages five hotels located across Tenerife, the largest of the Canary Islands. The company is a part of Grupo FEDOLA, a Tenerife-based business group with more than 20 diverse brands.

Global Payments Inc. (NYSE: GPN) is a leading provider of payment technology and software solutions delivering innovative services to customers globally. Headquartered in Atlanta, Georgia with more than 10,000 employees worldwide, Global Payments is a member of the S&P 500 with customers and partners in 30 countries throughout North America, Europe, the Asia-Pacific region, and Brazil.
Founded in 1998 in South Africa, Globeflight provides the business community with a full spectrum of transport and logistic services.
Founded in 1972, Governors’ Camp runs pioneering safaris across Kenya and Rwanda as well as seven properties, hot air-balloons and light aircraft.
Guidion connects its customers with expert engineers to install and repair domestic systems such as smart metering, telecoms, and central heating.

Hackney Council is a local government authority in East London that offers its residents and businesses a wide range of essential services such as road and waste management, social care, housing, and civil protection.

Hamilton Beach simplifies global email operations and saves 60%. With an outdated email system, mailbox storage that tripled in size and partners that needed a reliable email and file access, Hamilton Beach moved to G Suite.

Based in New Delhi, Hero MotoCorp is one of the world's largest makers of two-wheeler vehicles, with a production capacity of 9 million units from five manufacturing plants in India and one each in Colombia and Bangladesh. The business has more than 90 million customers and operates in 37 countries across Asia, Africa, and South and Central America. In its home market, HeroMotoCorp sells one in every two two-wheelers.

HK01 is on a mission to create a digital platform that combines real-time Hong Kong news and current affairs, commentary, and exclusive investigation reports, round the clock, as well as entertainment, and lifestyle services. With 33 million+ average page views daily and 2.77 million app downloads as of February 2020, it’s one of Hong Kong’s most popular online news sources. The company also distributes content through its weekly print edition. Dedicated to giving back to the local community, HK01 established Hong Kong's first charity fundraising platform, 01 Heart, in 2019 and raised nearly HK$2 million for 100+ charity projects that same year.
Homer Central School District serves the town of Homer, New York, operating four schools with approximately 1,750 students and 250 teachers.
Hunterdon Healthcare is a non-profit healthcare organization providing a full range of quality health and medical services to communities in northwest New Jersey.
Hurley Medical Center was founded in 1908 to serve Flint, Michigan residents. Its mission is to offer innovative, leading-edge technology and state-of-the-art facilities.
ibibo Group is a leading online travel company that includes the Goibibo hotel and air aggregator and the redBus online bus ticketing platform.
Founded in 1986, Interconnect Systems specialises in creating server rooms and computer cabling solutions for organisations across South Africa.

IT Convergence is a global consulting and services company that works with enterprise clients seeking to improve their internal IT infrastructure. With provider specialties for Oracle, IT Convergence guides clients through the entire update cycle from employee training to cloud architecture design and helps ensure that they can leverage technology to maximize competitiveness.
PR company, Jargon, increases productivity by 50% with G Suite.

Based in central Texas, JBGoodwin is a real estate agency that helps connect buyers, sellers, and renters to home opportunities. Founded in 1972, JBGoodwin maintains offices in Austin and San Antonio, Texas.
Jeni's Splendid Ice Creams is an artisan ice-cream company, known for its creative flavors and its high-quality ingredients.
KAESER COMPRESSORS has been providing compressed air systems solutions since 1919 and currently employs approximately 6,000 people throughout the world.

Founded in 1994, Kanbawza Bank (KBZ Bank) is Myanmar's largest privately owned bank with more than 20,000 employees and is the cornerstone of conglomerate KBZ Group, which has 80,000 employees. KBZ Bank combines commercial operations with national services, such as financial inclusion programs and maintaining unprofitable branches in remote communities. The bank has "metta" – a Buddhist value known as loving kindness – as a core value.

Founded in 1991 and headquartered in Victoria, Australia, Kings Transport is a transport and logistics provider specializing in contract logistics and express services. The company’s operations extend to Queensland, New South Wales, South Australia, Western Australia, and New Zealand.

column3: Kingston and Sutton London Borough Councils are local government authorities in southwest London that assist residents, local businesses, and visitors.

How Kisan Network uses G Suite to help Indian farmers reap more profits from
                  their crops
column3: Founded in 2015, Kisan Network is an agricultural supply chain company that connects farmers in India directly with the businesses they serve, empowering them to be paid fair prices.

Korean Air is a leading global airline with 169 aircraft and flies to 127 cities in 44 countries, including 13 cities in South Korea, as of December 2019. In line with its motto, “Excellence in Flight,” Korean Air is expanding its global networks by exploring the addition of new destinations and strengthening its international operations.

L&T Financial Services is a leading financial services company transforming lives in rural India with a core focus on rural, housing, and wholesale loans. Serving 11 million customers to date, L&T Financial Services leads the industry with fast turnaround times for loan approvals by adopting analytics and cloud technology.

L’Appart Fitness is a family-owned gym chain founded in 1997 in Lyon. The company is among the top five leaders in the French fitness market in terms of club numbers, and uses G Suite solutions to manage its growing employee and client base around the country.
Founded in 1881, civil engineering firm Léon Grosse has 2,300 employees between mainland France and French overseas territories and a consolidated revenue of €827 million (2017).
Located in the textile district of Nola in Italy, Liu Jo UOMO offers premium-quality men’s clothing through a range of outlets across Italy and Europe.

Manchester City Council is the local authority for the city of Manchester, part of the Greater Manchester Council Authority serving 2.7 million citizens in a busy metropolitan area with a unique history.

Mass Rapid Transit Corporation Sdn Bhd., fully owned by the Minister of Finance Incorporated, is the developer and asset owner of the Klang Valley Mass Rapid Transit (KVMRT) Project. Incorporated in 2011, Mass Rapid Transit Corporation is responsible for monitoring and tracking construction of all elevated structures, stations, and depots of the KVMRT project. The organization also manages below-ground works including the tunneling and construction of underground stations.
MatchMove develops secure digital wallet systems that businesses can rebrand and market to customers.

Founded in 2008, Maven Wave Partners is a Google Cloud Premier Partner. The Chicago-based company provides consulting and technology expertise to large enterprise customers, enabling their digital transformations through cloud solutions such as Google Cloud Platform.

McClatchy was founded in 1857 with the publication of its first newspaper, The Daily Bee, in Sacramento, California. Today, the company has transformed into a digital-first media enterprise, with local news outlets in 30 markets and 14 states in the United States providing each of its communities with independent local journalism in the public interest and advertising services in a wide array of digital and print formats. In total, McClatchy reporters have won 54 Pulitzer Prizes.

MediaNews Group is a leader in local, multi-platform news and information, distinguished by its award-winning, original content and high-quality, diversified portfolio of local media assets, including The Denver Post, San Jose Mercury News, and the Boston Herald. Based in Denver, the company has about 4,000 employees.
Founded in 2012, MightyHive provides programmatic advertising and marketing services to help businesses optimize every customer engagement.

MobileOne LLC operates more than 125 T-Mobile premium retail stores across the United States. Founded in 2008, MobileOne has been named to Inc. magazine’s list of the 5,000 fastest-growing private firms in the United States.
The MMFA welcomes a million visitors annually as Quebec’s most visited museum. It is one of the most popular museums in Canada, and ranks 18th among art museums in North America.
Morrisons is a large supermarket chain in the United Kingdom, headquartered in Bradford, West Yorkshire, England.

Multnomah County is the most populous of Oregon’s counties and is home to Portland, its largest city. In 2010, the county made the move to G Suite to support an increasingly mobile workforce. Since then, the county has scaled up to support 6,200 workers and encouraged them to move as many workflows to the cloud as possible.
MyRepublic is a multinational telecommunications and internet company headquartered in Singapore.

Operating 156 publications in more than 615 markets across 39 states, New Media Investment Group supports small to mid-size communities by providing locally focused print and digital content to over 22 million people on a weekly basis. The company also provides premier marketing and technology solutions to more than 200,000 business customers.

Northern Grampians Shire Council governs a vast rural area of 5,918 km2 in the Wimmera region of Victoria. It delivers more than 60 citizen services, such as family health, home, and community care, as well as business attraction, planning, recreation, infrastructure, waste management, and road services. It was one of the first Australian councils to fully migrate to Google solutions.
Nielsen is a global measurement and data analytics company that provides the most complete and trusted view available of consumers and markets worldwide.

NII Holdings is a provider of wireless communication services to millions of customers in Brazil, under the Nextel brand. It employs over 4,000 people, and its corporate headquarters is in Reston, Virginia.
Noberasco is an Italian leader in the food industry from Liguria, specialising in the dry and dried fruit sector.
Northumberland County Council is a unitary authority in North East England.

Nubian Skin launched in 2014 with a carefully edited collection of lingerie and hosiery for women of color. Headquartered in London, Nubian Skin sells online worldwide as well as in retail stores in the United Kingdom, Nigeria, and the United States.

With more than 20 years' experience, O2 Care Services offers in-home services such as cleaning and childcare. It is headquartered in Le Mans, France, and is part of the Oui Care Group, a French market leader.

Ocado delivers groceries with automation and the help of Google technology. While Ocado's primary focus is getting groceries from online orders to your door in excellent condition, it continue to push the limits of what technology can do to automate and scale business.
OIC Onlus is a non-profit foundation based in Veneto, Italy with 13 centres that bring care for the elderly, the very young, and the disabled together in one place.
The OLX Group operates a network of trading platforms in over 40 countries, creating win-win exchanges for people, communities, and the environment.

OrangeTee is a Singapore-based property and real estate business that has approximately 100 employees and works with about 4,100 property agents. The company provides a range of services, including property brokerage; support for residential and overseas projects; corporate leasing; property investments and advisory; a joint venture Japan business development unit; property research; and valuations.
Formed from a merger in 2003, Ospedali Riuniti di Ancona is a university hospital and one of central Italy’s leading providers of cardiothoracic surgery, neurosurgery, and emergency healthcare.

With pawn and loan financing as its main business, Pegadaian is expanding its market capitalization through digital products such as fintech lending. Its vision is to be Indonesia’s most valuable financial company and top financial inclusion agent.

PIK Group is the biggest residential developer in Russia and specializes in large-scale residential housing projects. Since its inception in 1994, PIK Group has built more than 300,000 apartments, totaling 19 million square meters of real estate.
A leading TLC company, Piramis sells and distributes Vodafone products as well as other communications software and services.

Founded in 1948, The Printers Mysore was the first newspaper and bilingual publisher of India’s Mysore State, now Karnataka. Today it serves 10.69M print readers and attracts 57M monthly page views from across the country.
Based in San Jose, California, Pulse Secure is a Google Technology Partner providing secure access and application delivery solutions to enterprises and service providers.

Quimmco is an industrial construction consortium that works in fields such as chemical production, metalworking, and precision machining. Founded in 1989 and with more than $1 billion in revenue, the family-owned business helps customers meet their challenges by emphasizing continuous innovation.
Founded in The Netherlands in 1960, Randstad is a multinational recruitment company with more than 4,000 branches in 39 countries worldwide.
Rawson Properties handles residential and commercial sales and lettings, auctions, and property developments with 200 franchises across South Africa.

RedDoorz is a fast-growing hotel management company that specializes in providing affordable accommodation. It currently has more than 1,000 hotels in four countries in the region under its brand, targeting young travelers to offer them the best accommodation within their budget range.

Owned by Unilab, RelianceUnited operates a network of outpatient healthcare businesses such as corporate clinics, primary care clinics, dialysis centers, and outpatient surgical centers to improve access to medical care in the Philippines.

From pest controllers to interior landscapers, Rentokil Initial is working better with Google. Since switching to G Suite, Rentokil Initial saved millions of pounds on time spent on IT maintenance and administrative tasks.

RLE International is known for its sophisticated engineering solutions in various fields including renewable energies, bionics, and transportation. Headquartered in Overath near Cologne, it has more than 2,000 employees worldwide.
The city of Rovaniemi is the capital of Lapland in Finland and the official home of Santa Claus, attracting hundreds of thousands of visitors every year from around the world.

The Royal Government of Bhutan pursues the vision of “gross national happiness” that balances development with well-being and sustainability. The Himalayan nation of 735,553 people is carbon-negative, nurtures a rich cultural heritage, and has won global acclaim for wildlife conservation that protects habitats for endangered species.
SADA Systems is a Google Cloud Premier Partner with proven expertise in Google Cloud consulting, migration and deployment, custom development, user adoption, and change management services.

A Google Cloud Premier Partner, Safetec is a pioneering consultancy in corporate cloud solutions, operating in North and Northeast Brazil. The Safetec mission is to help companies in all industries implement and use new collaboration and communication technologies to generate business value.

Salesforce is the world’s leading provider of Customer Relationship Management (CRM) software. The San Francisco-based company has offices worldwide and recently ranked number 1 in Fortune’s “100 Best Companies to Work For.”

Samudera Indonesia is an integrated cargo transportation and logistics company. The company has six business lines including shipping, logistics, ports, shipyards, property, and services. Samudera Indonesia has approximately 100 subsidiaries and 6,000 employees in offices across Indonesia and Asia.

Fortune 500 company Sanmina (NASDAQ: SANM) designs and manufactures complex optical, electronic, and mechanical products for some of the world’s most innovative companies. The company employs more than 45,000 people and has 75 manufacturing facilities worldwide.

Founded in St. Louis in 1939, Schnuck Markets, Inc. is a third-generation, family-owned grocery/pharmacy retailer committed to nourishing people’s lives. The company takes pride in its community partnerships and employs more than 13,000 teammates and operates 100 stores in Missouri, Illinois, Indiana, Wisconsin, and Iowa.

The Scotts Miracle-Gro Company is the world's largest marketer of branded consumer products for lawn and garden care and is backed by 150 years of expertise. The company's brands include Scotts, Miracle-Gro, and Ortho.
Seeff Properties is one of Southern Africa’s largest real estate companies, with more than 1,200 staff at 220 branches in nine countries.

The Serenissima Ristorazione Group is one of Italy’s leaders in the commercial and catering sector, with more than 7,000 employees, 13 associated companies, and a consolidated turnover of more than €300 million.
Shaw Industries, a leading commercial carpet and flooring provider, goes lean with Google.

Situated on the western shore of Lake Michigan and extending west to the woods and marshes of the Kettle Moraine, between Milwaukee to the south and Green Bay to the north, Sheboygan County, Wisconsin covers over 500 square miles that’s home to 115,000 residents.
A member company of Sompo Holdings, Sompo Insurance (Hong Kong) started operations in 1957 and specialises in property and casualty insurance.

For over 30 years, Specialty Lighting has supplied lighting products and design services for a variety of national and international retail chains, restaurant chains, hotels, resorts, auto dealerships, assisted living facilities, casinos, and corporations.

A leading media organization in Asia, SPH has embraced new ways of working to thrive in an age of digital disruption. Its portfolio includes newspapers, magazines, online portals, radio stations, as well as real estate and healthcare investments.
Located in the southwestern United States, Arizona is the 6th largest and the 14th most populous of the 50 states in the country.

column2: Insurance agency StreetSmart modernizes its family business with G Suite
column3: StreetSmart Insurance launched in 2004 in Freehold, N.J. to offer auto, home, and business insurance to local customers. After a career in restaurants and banking, Jimmy Ferrara opened the agency, which he now runs with his four children. The agency has 17 employees in New Jersey, California, India, and the Philippines.
Team Olivia is a social care provider in Sweden, Norway and Denmark, delivering home care and rehabilitation services.

The Football Association of England (known as The FA) is the oldest football association in the world. Formed in 1863, it acts as the governing organization for the country's grassroots club programs up through the national teams, managing 33,000 players worldwide.
Founded in 1887, The Queen’s Fund provides grants to help women and children in Victoria, Australia, who are in crisis, distressed, or experiencing an emergency.
The Roche Group, a multinational healthcare company, wanted a single product for employees to work better together, from anywhere. G Suite helped meet this need.

The Weather Company forecasts clear skies with G Suite. Each portion of the business was working as an independent entity, so getting everyone under the same technological umbrella with G Suite was critical.

Thirdware’s expertise in manufacturing, specifically in the automotive industry, enables it to successfully deliver purpose-led, transformative solutions to help original equipment manufacturers (OEMs) and auto-component manufacturers worldwide. The company works to deliver superior results on its clients’ technology investments by solving complex business challenges, efficiently and to high standards. Thirdware’s team of 850 is headquartered in Mumbai, with offices in Chennai and Detroit.

ThoughtWorks is a pioneering software company, using an agile delivery approach to create client-focused software solutions. It has more than 5,000 employees across 14 countries, working with commercial, government, and social organizations. Its mission is to better humanity through software.
Toolquip & Allied provides engineering products, tools, and solutions through its retail outlets across South Africa.
Founded in 1999, Trade Me is the most popular online marketplace and classified advertising platform in New Zealand.
Founded in 1996, Tradebridge provides secure messaging solutions for financial transactions and healthcare information for organizations and consumers in South Africa.
TransContainer is a Russian container operator managing the largest fleet of containers and railway logistics equipment in Russia.
Travis Perkins is a British builders' merchant and home improvement retailer based in Northampton.

TrueCar, Inc. is an online automotive marketplace platform that helps buyers connect with dealers to purchase new and used cars. With a network of more than 14,000 authorized dealers and features such as in-depth price trend analysis, TrueCar simplifies the car buying process for its customers and partners.

Twinkl is an online publishing platform with educational content designed for anyone who teaches, inside or outside the classroom. It's planning and assessment resources enable parents, teachers, schools, and nurseries to easily tailor content and quickly select appropriate child-centered materials, saving time and supporting children's learning.
The United Kingdom Health Department is responsible for government policy on health and adult social care matters.

Founded more than 50 years ago and headquartered in Kolkata, India, Usha Martin is a leading steel and wire rope manufacturer. The company’s products are used in sectors such as oil and gas, aerial haulage, and general engineering.

column2: Vichy Catalan Corporation rejuvenates its workforce with more than mineral water
column3: Vichy Catalan Corporation is made up of three main business concerns: drinks manufacturing, drinks distribution, and the Vichy Catalan Corporation Hotel & Spa.
Viessmann is one of the world's leading manufacturers of energy systems. A family-owned company, it is based in Allendorf, Germany, and operates worldwide.
With 35 locations throughout Italy, Virgin Active offers a premium health club experience, helping its 160,000 members be their personal best.

Vonage (NYSE:VG) is redefining business communications. True to its roots as a technology disruptor, Vonage embraced technology to transform how companies communicate to create better business outcomes. The company's unique cloud communications platform brings together a robust unified communications solution with the agility of embedded contextual communications APIs. This powerful combination enables businesses to collaborate more productively and engage their customers more effectively across messaging, chat, social media, video, and voice.
Weiss + Appetito group offers construction services in Switzerland, Germany, Austria, and France, ranging from flooring to specialised industrial transportation.
Whirlpool Corporation moves to G Suite to build its “winning workplace." Learn how Whirlpool faces the challenge of faster innovations in this competitive market.
Xero develops online accounting software.

For more than 55 years, York has been delivering results clients can see and feel. As a leading risk solutions provider, the company serves corporations, the insurance industry, and public entities to reduce risk and drive high-quality outcomes. It does this by offering integrated and customized solutions including risk management, claims administration, managed care, and absence management. With its data-driven and compassionate approach, York delivers on its mission of reducing risk and getting people and organizations back to health, work, and productivity.

Founded in 2012, Zalora is an online retailer that sells fashion to customers in Hong Kong, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, and Taiwan. Zalora has about 26 million users of its websites and mobile applications in the region.
